ZH: 飞机即将开始降落。
EN: The plane is about to begin its descent.

ZH: 请确保您的座椅在飞机降落前处于直立位置。
EN: Please make sure your seat is in the upright position before the plane lands.

ZH: 飞机已经安全降落在台北机场。
EN: The plane has safely landed at Taipei Airport.

ZH: 时间紧迫，我们必须尽快降落。
EN: Time is running out, we need to land as soon as possible.

ZH: 需要耐心等待，飞机即将降落。
EN: Please be patient, the plane will be landing soon.

ZH: 飞行员紧紧抓住控制杆，准备进行降落。
EN: The pilot grips the control stick tightly, preparing for landing.

ZH: 飞机在浓雾中降落，非常危险。
EN: It is very dangerous for the plane to land in thick fog.

ZH: 降落过程中请系好安全带。
EN: Please fasten your seatbelt during landing.

ZH: 飞机正要开始降落，乘客们请回到座位上。
EN: The plane is about to start its descent, passengers please return to your seats.

ZH: 飞机即将降落，乘客们请注意听从机组人员指示。
EN: The plane will be landing soon, passengers please pay attention to the instructions of the crew.

ZH: 这个机场的降落跑道非常长。
EN: The runway at this airport is very long.

ZH: 飞机降落时会感觉到明显的减速。
EN: There will be a noticeable deceleration when the plane lands.

ZH: 飞机即将降落，机组人员请做好准备。
EN: The plane is about to land, crew members please prepare.

ZH: 火箭顺利降落在月球表面。
EN: The rocket successfully landed on the surface of the moon.

ZH: 下雪的时候，飞机降落会变得更加困难。
EN: Landing a plane becomes more difficult when it snows.

ZH: 飞机在海面上降落，然后停在码头上。
EN: The plane landed on the sea and then docked at the pier.

ZH: 正在飞往纽约的飞机将在大约一个小时后降落。
EN: The plane flying to New York will land in approximately one hour.

ZH: 飞机降落后，乘客们欢呼雀跃。
EN: Passengers cheer and applaud when the plane lands.

ZH: 飞机顺利降落后，乘客们赞扬机组的出色表现。
EN: Passengers praise the excellent performance of the crew after a smooth landing.

ZH: 飞机终于降落在离目的地不远的机场。
EN: The plane finally lands at an airport not far from its destination.
